{"lemma":"عَظِيم","slug":"عَظِيم","root":"ع.ظ.م","root_slug":"ع-ظ-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ظ-م","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَظِيم","root":"عظم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":107},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29682","n29683"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B8%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"magnificent, grandiose"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"great"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"powerful","examples":[{"text":"اللَّهُ لَا إِلَهَ إِلَّا هُوَ الْحَيُّ الْقَيُّومُ لَا تَأْخُذُهُ سِنَةٌ وَلَا نَوْمٌ لَهُ مَا فِي السَّمَاوَاتِ وَمَا فِي الْأَرْضِ مَنْ ذَا الَّذِي يَشْفَعُ عِنْدَهُ إِلَّا بِإِذْنِهِ يَعْلَمُ مَا بَيْنَ أَيْدِيهِمْ وَمَا خَلْفَهُمْ وَلَا يُحِيطُونَ بِشَيْءٍ مِنْ عِلْمِهِ إِلَّا بِمَا شَاءَ وَسِعَ كُرْسِيُّهُ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالْأَرْضَ وَلَا يَئُودُهُ حِفْظُهُمَا وَهُوَ الْعَلِيُّ الْعَظِيمُ","english":"Allah - there is no deity except Him, the Ever-Living, the Sustainer of [all] existence. Neither drowsiness overtakes Him nor sleep. To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Who is it that can intercede with Him except by His permission? He knows what is [presently] before them and what will be after them, and they encompass not a thing of His knowledge except for what He wills. His Kursi extends over the heavens and the earth, and their preservation tires Him not. And He is the Most High, the Most Great."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"large, big"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb عَظِمَ (ʕaẓima, “to become great”). Related to Hebrew עָצוּם ('atsúm, “enormous, colossal”)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.ðˤiːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29682","headword_ar":"عَظِيمٌ","root":"EZm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having the quality denoted by the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZuma","text_ar":"عَظُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great, big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;] (S, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuZaAmN","text_ar":"عُظَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA) in an intensive sense [i. e. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very great"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuZ~aAmN","text_ar":"عُظَّامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) in a more intensive sense than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuZaAmN","text_ar":"عُظَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very very great"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZiymN","text_ar":"عَظِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"esteemed great"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by another"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabiyrN","text_ar":"كَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies “ great &c. in itself: ” (El-Fakhr Er-Rázee, TA:) or the former is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaqiyrN","text_ar":"حَقِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [i. e. it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of great account"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaqiyrN","text_ar":"حَقِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is inferior to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SagiyrN","text_ar":"صَغِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZiymN","text_ar":"عَظِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is superior to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabiyrN","text_ar":"كَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ksh and Bd in ii. 6;) and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, in comparison with other things of its kind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ibid:) [it may therefore often be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"huge, enormous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"used metaphorically, as applied to an object of the intellect, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great in estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and thus as applied to a man: also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of great magnitude"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"importance: of great gravity: difficult, hard, severe, grievous, distressing, afflictive, troublesome,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burdensome:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 6:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"formidable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"terrible."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2088},{"kind":"text","text":"xxii. 1.) Hence one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN EaZiymN fiY Almajodi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ عَظِيمٌ فِى المَجْدِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlr~aA^oYi","text_ar":"وَالرَّاْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man great in respect of glory, honour, dignity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility, and of judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAhu biEaZiymK","text_ar":"رَمَاهُ بِعَظِيمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimuEoZamK","text_ar":"بِمُعْظَمٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reproached him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upbraided him, with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he accused him of, a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act, of great gravity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an enormity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: both mean the same. (TA.) [The pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZiymN","text_ar":"عَظِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiZaAmN","text_ar":"عِظَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, applied to rational beings,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuZamaA='u","text_ar":"عُظَمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaZiymu","text_ar":"العَظِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to God is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkabiyru","text_ar":"الكَبِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Incomparably-great"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n29683","headword_ar":"عُظَيْمٌ","root":"EZm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuZayomu waD~aAHK","text_ar":"عُظَيْمُ وَضَّاحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZomN","text_ar":"عَظْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}